description:
Indonesia is in talks with China to restructure debt linked to its $7.3 billion high-speed rail project, Whoosh  the first bullet train in Southeast Asia. Built under Chinas Belt and Road Initiative, the JakartaBandung line was launched in 2023 but is now operating at a loss, with low passenger numbers and high costs. Indonesias sovereign wealth fund, Danantara, is leading debt talks as the government rules out using public funds. China calls the project a success, but Indonesias losses highlight wider struggles, as countries from Zambia to Sri Lanka seek to renegotiate Chinese loans amid mounting repayment pressures.
